  "text": "The xDS v3 transport protocol implementation in Envoy is located in source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/. The key components are:\n\n1. GrpcSubscriptionImpl (grpc_subscription_impl.h/cc): The adapter that bridges typed Subscription to the untyped GrpcMux interface. It handles per-xDS API stats and logging for configuration subscriptions.\n\n2. GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory (grpc_subscription_factory.h/cc): The factory class that creates subscriptions and selects between SotW (State of the World) and Delta xDS modes based on runtime features. When the runtime feature 'envoy.reloadable_features.unified_mux' is enabled, it uses the new unified XdsMux template implementations (GrpcMuxSotw/GrpcMuxDelta), otherwise it uses the legacy implementations (GrpcMuxImpl for SotW, NewGrpcMuxImpl for Delta).\n\n3. Legacy SotW Implementation - GrpcMuxImpl (grpc_mux_impl.h/cc): The original State of the World xDS implementation that handles the traditional xDS protocol where the server sends complete resource snapshots.\n\n4. Legacy Delta Implementation - NewGrpcMuxImpl (new_grpc_mux_impl.h/cc): The Delta xDS implementation that handles incremental updates. It uses DeltaSubscriptionState to track protocol state and manages subscriptions through a WatchMap.\n\n5. Unified XdsMux Template (xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h/cc): A template-based implementation with parameters S (subscription state type), F (subscription state factory), RQ (request type), and RS (response type). This unified mux supports both SotW and Delta modes through specialization:\n   - GrpcMuxSotw: Specialization using SotwSubscriptionState for SotW protocol\n   - GrpcMuxDelta: Specialization using DeltaSubscriptionState for Delta protocol\n\n6. Subscription State Classes:\n   - SotwSubscriptionState (xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.h/cc): Tracks state-of-the-world xDS protocol session state\n   - DeltaSubscriptionState (xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.h/cc): Tracks delta xDS protocol session state with incremental resource tracking\n\nThe factory pattern in GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory enables seamless switching between the old and new unified implementations through the 'envoy.reloadable_features.unified_mux' runtime feature, allowing for gradual migration and testing of the new unified template-based approach."
}

